<h1><a name="Exercises"></a> Exercises </h1>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Prerequisite"></a> Prerequisite </span></h2>
<p /> <ul>
<li> Login on submission node <pre class="screen">
ssh user@osg-ss-submit.chtc.wisc.edu
</pre>
</li></ul> 
<!--   * Initialize the OSG client environment <pre class="screen">
source /opt/osg-client/setup.sh
</pre>
--> <ul>
<li> Obtain proxy certificate, if you have not done so already <pre class="screen">
voms-proxy-init -voms osgedu:/osgedu
</pre>
</li> <li> Make a working directory for this exercise<pre class="screen">
mkdir -p /home/user/dm_part_3
cd /home/user/dm_part_3
</pre>
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Using_an_HTTP_Proxy"></a> Using an HTTP Proxy </span></h2>
<p />
To successfully use a HTTP cache, three things need to be done: <ol>
<li> A file must be uploaded to a source HTTP site (this is known as "staging").
</li> <li> The location of the cache must be known.
</li> <li> The file must be downloaded by an HTTP client using cache-friendly headers.
</li></ol> 
<p />
We will do these in this exercise, then we will return to the previous BLAST example.
<p />
<h3><a name="Staging_Files"></a> Staging Files </h3>
<p />
In the simplest setup, a web server can export a directory on the file system.  To make a file accessible, you simply need to know the directory name and copy the file into it.
<p />
For this tutorial, we run the Apache web server and have the directory <code><b>~/public_html</b></code> exported to the URL <code><b>http://osg-ss-submit.chtc.wisc.edu/~user</b></code>.  The HTTP proxy software is called Squid and is running on osg-ss-se.chtc.wisc.edu:3128.  First, create your <code><b>~/public_html</b></code> in your home directory:
<pre class="screen">
mkdir -p ~/public_html
</pre>
<p />
Then, write a simple file into this directory:
<pre class="screen">
echo 'Hello world!' > ~/public_html/hello_world.txt
</pre>
<p />
Now, redirect your browser to <a href="http://osg-ss-submit.chtc.wisc.edu/~user/hello_world.txt" target="_top">http://osg-ss-submit.chtc.wisc.edu/~user/hello_world.txt</a>; you should see the text <code>Hello world!</code>.
<p />
<h3><a name="Finding_an_HTTP_Proxy"></a> Finding an HTTP Proxy </h3>
<p />
There are three ways to determine an HTTP proxy: <ol>
<li> (Linux standard) Look into the value of <code><b>$http_proxy</b></code> in the running environment.
</li> <li> (OSG-specific) On a worker node, the HTTP proxy will be set in <code><b>$OSG_SQUID_LOCATION</b></code>.  If there is no proxy available, <code><b>$OSG_SQUID_LOCATION</b></code> will be unset or set to <code><b>UNAVAILABLE</b></code>.
</li> <li> Manually hard-code the location of a proxy in application code.
</li></ol> 
<p />
All HTTP clients packaged with the OSG will look at the value of <code><b>$http_proxy</b></code>.
<p />
From the login node osg-ss-submit.chtc.wisc.edu, the correct value of <code><b>http_proxy</b></code> is:
<p />
<pre class="screen">
export http_proxy=osg-ss-se.chtc.wisc.edu:3128
</pre>
<p />
Set this in your environment now.
<p />
GlideinWMS automatically exports the <code>OSG_SQUID_LOCATION</code> to the <code>http_proxy</code> environment variable.  The logic is as below.  You do not need to execute the following:
<p />
<pre class="file">
export OSG_SQUID_LOCATION=${OSG_SQUID_LOCATION:-UNAVAILABLE}
if [ "$OSG_SQUID_LOCATION" != UNAVAILABLE ]; then
  export http_proxy=$OSG_SQUID_LOCATION
fi
</pre>
<p />
<h3><a name="Using_an_HTTP_Proxy_AN1"></a> Using an HTTP Proxy </h3>
<p />
Copy the <code>yeast.aa.psq</code> database file into <code><b>~/public_html</b></code>.  First, verify <code><b>$http_proxy</b></code> is set:
<pre class="screen">
[user@osg-ss-submit dm_part_3]$ echo $http_proxy
osg-ss-se.chtc.wisc.edu:3128
</pre>
<p />
Now, download the file using <code>wget</code>.  We'll add the <code>-d</code> flag to get extra debug information:
<pre class="screen">
wget "http://osg-ss-submit.chtc.wisc.edu/~user/yeast.aa.psq" -d
</pre>
<div class="twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline">  <span id="twistyIdEducationOSGSS2013StorageEx31show" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleopen-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Show output</span></a> </span> <span id="twistyIdEducationOSGSS2013StorageEx31hide" class="twistyTrigger twikiUnvisited twistyHidden twistyInited"><a href="#"><img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/toggleclose-small.gif" border="0" alt="" /><span class="twikiLinkLabel twikiUnvisited">Hide output</span></a> </span>  </div><!--/twistyPlugin twikiMakeVisibleInline--> <div class="twistyPlugin"><div id="twistyIdEducationOSGSS2013StorageEx31toggle" class="twistyContent twikiMakeHidden twistyInited">
